@page
@model LogiDocs.Web.Pages.PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="app-page">
    <div class="dashboard-card">
        <div class="dashboard-card-header mb-3">
            <div>
                <h1 class="display-6 fw-bold mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
                <p class="text-muted mb-0">
                    Information about how LogiDocs processes, stores, and protects platform data.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <section class="mb-4">
            <h4 class="fw-bold mb-2">Overview</h4>
            <p class="mb-0">
                LogiDocs is a web platform designed to manage transport records, logistics documents,
                and document validation workflows. The system supports document upload, integrity
                verification, role-based access, and monitoring of transport-related processes.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-4">
            <h4 class="fw-bold mb-2">Data We Collect</h4>
            <p>
                The platform may process user account data, transport information, uploaded
                logistics documents, document hashes generated for integrity verification,
                document statuses, transport statuses, and workflow-related actions performed
                by authorized users.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-0">
                Uploaded files are stored within the application environment and are linked
                to the corresponding transport and document records.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-4">
            <h4 class="fw-bold mb-2">Purpose of Data Processing</h4>
            <p>
                Data is processed in order to support the core functionality of the application,
                including transport registration, document management, integrity verification,
                validation workflows, and controlled access to information based on user roles.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-0">
                Hash values are generated to support document integrity checks and to detect
                possible modifications to stored files.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-4">
            <h4 class="fw-bold mb-2">Access and User Roles</h4>
            <p>
                Access to information in LogiDocs is restricted according to user roles.
                Depending on permissions, users may upload documents, register them in the
                validation workflow, verify integrity, validate records, or reject documents.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-0">
                Role-based access helps ensure that only authorized users can perform specific
                operations or view protected records.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-4">
            <h4 class="fw-bold mb-2">Data Protection</h4>
            <p>
                LogiDocs applies authentication and access control mechanisms to protect system
                data. Documents are stored in a structured environment, and integrity control
                is supported through generated SHA-256 hashes.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-0">
                The application is designed to reduce unauthorized access and to preserve the
                consistency of transport and document records.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-4">
            <h4 class="fw-bold mb-2">Blockchain Notice</h4>
            <p class="mb-0">
                In the current version of the system, blockchain registration is simulated for
                demonstration and development purposes. The platform may be extended in the future
                to support real blockchain integration for document traceability and authenticity
                confirmation.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-4">
            <h4 class="fw-bold mb-2">Data Retention</h4>
            <p class="mb-0">
                Records and uploaded documents are retained for as long as they are required for
                the operation of the platform, testing activities, or administrative review, in
                accordance with the rules defined for the system.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-4">
            <h4 class="fw-bold mb-2">User Rights</h4>
            <p class="mb-0">
                Authorized users may request access to relevant information, correction of inaccurate
                records, or removal of data where such actions are permitted by the application rules
                and administrative policies.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h4 class="fw-bold mb-2">Contact Information</h4>
            <p class="mb-0">
                For questions regarding privacy, data handling, or access to information stored in
                LogiDocs, users should contact the platform administrator.
            </p>
        </section>
    </div>
</div>